245
00:17:11,867 --> 00:17:14,290
So economists call this thinking on the margin.

246
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:15,351
On the margin.

247
00:17:15,851 --> 00:17:20,537
So we want to make decisions incrementally.

248
00:17:20,877 --> 00:17:30,968
It's easier to think incrementally to break a how many decision down into a series of smaller or marginal decisions like, should I have one more?

249
00:17:31,609 --> 00:17:36,611
So did I properly think on the margin there, the value of each additional chicken McNuggets?

250
00:17:36,631 --> 00:17:40,233
Yeah, because the price in terms of dollars was zero.

251
00:17:40,493 --> 00:17:41,854
Which we call the marginal cost.

252
