257
00:18:08,955 --> 00:18:16,119
I'm thinking the cost of one more thing, the benefit, the utility, the joy I get from one more thing.

258
00:18:16,500 --> 00:18:17,560
I'm balancing these two.

259
00:18:18,281 --> 00:18:20,282
How do we add this all together for decisions?

260
00:18:20,884 --> 00:18:30,166
So the key idea of the marginal principle is it just provides a simple rule of thumb to help you think through getting the most you can out of life.

261
00:18:30,806 --> 00:18:42,689
