265
00:18:51,775 --> 00:18:56,756
Well, the answer is you want to make any choice where the marginal benefit exceeds the marginal cost.

266
00:18:57,456 --> 00:19:05,459
If you take every opportunity where marginal benefit exceeds marginal cost, the very last opportunity that's left is the one where the marginal benefit equals marginal cost.

267
00:19:05,579 --> 00:19:12,361
So you know that from the cost benefit principle that if the benefits exceed the cost, it's a good choice.

268
00:19:13,401 --> 00:19:19,865
And so when you apply that marginal principle, you think incrementally on the margin.

